Vol / Page:  155
Edition:
Quote:  In those days [early 1900s] the [kauri bushmen's] customary dress was the old Blucher boots ... and tairoa trousers, which were made of a kind of heavy white duck; these were tied with bowyangs below the knees.
Notes:   (Joe Gasparich, Northland kauri country)

